Citation.sTitle: Measurement and Correlation for Solubility of Thiourea in Triglycol + Water at Temperatures from (292.05 to 357.75) K
Citation.sAbstract: The solubility of thiourea in triglycol + water had been determined from (292.05 to 357.75) K by the synthetic method. The experimental data were correlated with the modified Apelblat equation.
